\]

At pH = 7.00, \([\ce{H^{+}}]=10^{-7}\ \text{M}\).  
Carbonate speciation:

\[
\begin{aligned}
\ce{CO3^{2-} + H^{+} &<=> HCO3^{-}},\qquad 
K_{a2}=4.7\times10^{-11}\\[2pt]
\ce{HCO3^{-} + H^{+} &<=> H2CO3},\qquad 
K_{a1}=4.3\times10^{-7}
\end{aligned}
\]

Let \(x=[\ce{CO3^{2-}}]\). Then  

\[
\begin{aligned}
[\ce{HCO3^{-}}] &= \frac{[\ce{H^{+}}]\,x}{K_{a2}}\\[4pt]
[\ce{H2CO3}] &= \frac{[\ce{H^{+}}]^2\,x}{K_{a1}K_{a2}}
\end{aligned}
\]

The total dissolved carbonate (which equals the molar solubility \(s\)) is  

\[
s = x + \frac{[\ce{H^{+}}]\,x}{K_{a2}} + \frac{[\ce{H^{+}}]^2\,x}{K_{a1}K_{a2}}
      = x\!\left(1+\frac{[\ce{H^{+}}]}{K_{a2}}+\frac{[\ce{H^{+}}]^2}{K_{a1}K_{a2}}\right)
\]

Define  

\[
D = 1+\frac{[\ce{H^{+}}]}{K_{a2}}+\frac{[\ce{H^{+}}]^2}{K_{a1}K_{a2}}
\]

so that \(x = s/D\).  
Using the solubility product,

\[
K_{sp}=s\,x = \frac{s^{2}}{D}\;\;\Longrightarrow\;\;
s = \sqrt{K_{sp}\,D}
\]

